The paper proposes a new model for segmenting cells in microscopy images, which involves low-rank and structured sparse matrix decomposition and deconvolution. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision and image processing, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image restoration and filtering, which are also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed model involves optimization and algorithm design, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
